component.illusobjdesc:
There are five(?) figures in the left margin (top to bottom): 

                     a gowned woman 
standing with her (left?) arm raised vertically, and her other arm at her side, beside the second stanza; 

a tiny leaping(?) or flying figure with arms bent upward next to "Hover" 
(line 12), and just beneath it a sitting, hunched over figure; 

                     a seated, gowned, hunched over figure, with head lowered
                     and at least one arm on its lap, left of the fifth stanza; 

                     and, beside the sixth stanza, a standing figure, 
                     facing right, with its arm raised and one leg extended backward.
